# 4. あの時のこと

Miku: So, you've already had your meeting...?!
Rin: Then, all that's left is the actual shoot... This is so exciting!
MEIKO: I know it's not going to be easy, so we'll understand if you feel a little nervous. However, we're very much looking forward to seeing your beautiful smiles on TV!
Airi: Thanks! We're gonna prep as much as we can leading up to it!
Airi: Which means... We have to start brainstorming what could come our way.
Shizuku: Right. They may've provided us with a script, but the producer did mention how surprises are always welcome.
Haruka: We don't know what the Cheerful * Days MCs are going to throw at us, so we need to be prepared to answer some unexpected questions.
KAITO: Speaking of which... You met with Cheerful * Days at the TV station, yes?
Len: What were they like...? It was your first time seeing them after you left, right, Shizuku?
Shizuku: Yes. I was a little nervous at first, but I managed.
Shizuku: We greeted each other like normal and agreed to do everything we can for our shoot...
Airi: If I'm gonna be honest, that left a pretty bad taste in my mouth...
Airi: I mean, they said some really awful things about you, Shizuku. The least they could do is apologize.
Minori: Airi...
Airi: Still, it seemed like it was more or less all water under the bridge, which is good...
Shizuku: Yes...
Haruka: Also, about Higure... She became the lead after you left, right, Shizuku?
Shizuku: Yes, Arisa...
Shizuku: She has a very strong sense of responsibility and has this talent for pulling everybody in the right direction. Which is why when I saw that she had become the new lead, I thought she was the perfect person for the job.
Shizuku: Is something wrong?
Airi: Is something wrong...? I'm flabbergasted by how you can praise her after she said all those atrocious things about you.
Airi: But I guess that's just who you are... I'd never be able to do that.
Shizuku: I'm saying this because she really is a hard-working person.
Shizuku: Also, I don't think they were wrong about what they said about me back then...
Minori: What...?
Member A: Shizuku got another solo photo shoot for a magazine cover. This is clearly favoritism.
Member B: Yeah, I guess a pretty face is all they care about. We're clearly better at singing and dancing than she is.
Shizuku: It always took me more time than the others to master new songs and dances...
Shizuku: Not only that, but I always needed their help whenever we appeared on TV or did shows and such. I have a hard time saying that I was suited to be the lead.
Luka: Shizuku...
Shizuku: Oh, I'm sorry... I didn't mean for you to all feel so worried.
Luka: No, it's just... That must've been such an ordeal...
Shizuku: It was nothing, really... I don't think it was me who had it tough, but rather...
Shizuku: Actually, why don't I take this opportunity to tell you more about what happened between me and Cheerful * Days?
Airi: What...?
Minori: B-But... Are you sure...? Doesn't that mean you have to reopen some old wounds...?
Shizuku: It's okay...
Shizuku: If anything, I want you all to know. I believe this will help clear the air and allow us to properly prepare for our shoot.
Haruka: Shizuku...
Airi: Alright... If you're okay with this, we're listening.
Shizuku: Thank you...
Shizuku: I'm sure you already know this, but I joined Cheerful * Days after auditioning for them...
Shizuku: When I first joined this agency, I was billed more often as the “Grand Prix winner” as opposed to the new member of Cheerful * Days.
Shizuku: I remember being so busy too. I was constantly asked to do interviews on TV and short segments for certain shows...
Shizuku: So, I wasn't able to meet the other girls who joined at the same time as me until much later... But it was a very memorable moment for me.
Producer: This is the most recent Grand Prix winner. Shizuku Hinomori.
Producer: She's a member of the third generation just like all of you and will be joining you on stage moving forward. I hope you'll give her a warm welcome.
Shizuku: H-Hello. My name is Shizuku Hinomori... I apologize for not introducing myself sooner.
Shizuku: I, um... Unlike the rest of you, I don't have any experience in the entertainment industry... But I'm hoping to learn what I can as we go along...!
Group Members: Nice to meet you, Shizuku!
Group Members: This is a little odd since we're members of the same generation, but I've been following you on TV. I actually saw you earlier today! Let's do our best together!
Shizuku: Yes, of course...! Thank you very much!
Arisa: Hehe. We're the same generation and the same age, so there's no need to be so formal.
Shizuku: (Oh, that girl...)
Arisa: You're wondering if we've met before, yes...? I was the runner-up in the Grand Prix just behind you.
Shizuku: Yes, I remember. You're Arisa Higure, yes? You're so cute, and such a good singer and dancer... You definitely left a big impression on me.
Arisa: Really? But that's coming from the girl with the most brilliant aura of all time.
Shizuku: Oh... I'm sorry. I didn't mean to...
Arisa: Haha. Sorry, I was just pulling your leg!
Shizuku: Huh? Um...
Arisa: Again, there's no need to act so formal here. After all, we're members of the same group. Also...
Arisa: I lost the audition, but I'm going to become a select member no matter what. So, I want you to also give it everything you have.
Arisa: Let's do our best to make it so everyone calls the third generation the best ever in the history of Cheerful * Days, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Oh...
Shizuku: Yes, let's...!
Shizuku: That was the first time I met everyone... Arisa in particular was a powerful figure that I believe would be leading others someday.
Shizuku: From there on, I began learning more about the entertainment industry while receiving a long list of offers.
Shizuku: Everyone was very nice... We always had so much fun while waiting backstage or in the green room.
Shizuku: Then, one day... We were told that we'd be releasing a new song. Something different and not in our usual genre...
Shizuku: The dance for it was much more dynamic than usual, which I struggled just to memorize... But the others also had a hard time.
Shizuku: Huff... Huff...
Group Members: *Sigh* I'm exhausted! The dance for this song's way too hard!
Group Members: Honestly, I'm struggling to just keep up. I don't even have the time to see what everyone else is doing... And this is the opening number for our show? How are we going to get through it?
Shizuku: (I knew this song wasn't going to be easy to learn, but the others are also struggling... And they're by far way better dancers than I am...)
Shizuku: (Am I actually keeping up with them...?)
Arisa: Hey, whining won't get us anywhere. We have to get this completely down before our show.
Group Members: *Sob* We know that, but...
Arisa: Alright, cheer up. I mean, don't forget that we've overcome a lot as a group already.
Arisa: So, why don't we all go out for some barbeque today? We've been practicing nonstop for a while now, so I think we deserve a little break.
Group Members: B-Barbeque?! Yeah! Let's go!
Arisa: Alright, let's go! How about you, Shizuku...?!
Shizuku: Oh, I...
Shizuku: I'd like to go, but... I really need to practice this routine a little more.
Group Members: Wait, you're still gonna practice? But it's already getting pretty late.
Shizuku: I know... But I'm not as good at dancing as the rest of you, so I need to practice more to keep up...
Arisa: Then, I'll join you! I can't go knowing that you're going to be practicing!
Group Members: Wait, Arisa, what about barbeque?!
Group Members: We practiced so much today! And I've got a huge craving for barbeque now!
Arisa: Yes, but...
Shizuku: Don't mind me. Please go ahead.
Shizuku: I'd rather not keep you behind since you've already mastered it, Arisa.
Arisa: No, I really haven't... Some parts still definitely need work...
Group Members: But breaks are important too, right? Shizuku's giving us the green light, so let's go stuff our faces!
Arisa: Alright, fine. Let's go...
Arisa: Please don't push yourself too hard, Shizuku. We really don't want you to get injured in the process.
Shizuku: Thank you. I promise to be careful, so please go have fun.
Shizuku: *Sigh* As unfortunate as it is that I can't join them, I need to keep practicing.
Shizuku: (Since learning the dance routine as a whole has taken up so much of my time, I'm still struggling to master the details.)
Shizuku: (I can somewhat do the dance... But at this rate, I won't look very good on stage.)
Shizuku: So...
Shizuku: Let's keep trying!
Shizuku: I'll start again from the top and do what the dance teacher said. Move with grace and elegance...
Shizuku: And I'm not moving my hips very well for this part. I need to flow with the rhythm...
Producer: ...
Staff: Huh? Sir, what are you doing here?
Producer: Hmm... You've been watching these girls for quite a while now. Tell me. What do you think of Hinomori?
Staff: What do I think...? She has this incredible aura. I mean, she outshined all the others during their first show.
Staff: And I love how she has this incredible work ethic. Also, she can also be a little clumsy sometimes, so I think that contrast makes her more appealing...
Staff: In that sense, she may end up garnering the support of the more hardcore fans as opposed to the casual ones.
Producer: Which is a problem...
Producer: Hinomori won the Grand Prix because so many people were compelled by her perfect looks. To them, she's a beautiful but delicate flower that can accomplish anything flawlessly...
Producer: As a result, she's received more media exposure than anyone else from the third generation. So, we can't afford to disappoint everyone.
Staff: But...
Producer: That's why we need to find a new way to bill her. If we don't, her fifteen minutes as the Grand Prix winner will be over before we know it.
Producer: Nobody wants to see Hinomori the clumsy girl...
